What We Do

Raytheon provides state-of-the-art electronics, mission systems integration and other capabilities in the areas of sensing; effects; and command, control, communications and intelligence systems; as well as a broad range of mission support services.
View an alphabetical listing of our major products and services.

 
Missile Defense
Protecting our homeland. Defending our allies. Safeguarding trade. Our missile defense systems have one mission: providing peace of mind.
  Read more >>



Command and Control
Directing artillery. Routing aircraft. Flying satellites. When it comes to making order from disorder, nobody helps you complete the mission better than Raytheon.
 Read more >>



Sensors and Imaging
Peering deep into space. Scanning the vast seas. Monitoring the world's weather. Our sensor and imaging technologies have one mission: detecting the undetected.
 Read more >>



Cyber
Hackers. Worms. Trojan horses. Nobody understands the dangers of cyberspace like Raytheon.
Read more >>


 
Electronic Warfare
Creating ghosts. Making allies invisible. Turning out the lights on the enemy. Raytheon leads the development and production of electronic warfare solutions for the U.S. Army, Navy, Air Force and their international counterparts.
 Read more >>



Precision Weapons
Avoiding casualties. Reducing risk. Minimizing collateral damage. In a new era of warfare, our precision weapons are meeting the mission—hitting the target and nothing else.
 Read more >>



Training
With decades of experience and cutting-edge technologies, Raytheon delivers training solutions that help a wide range of government, military and commercial customers build and maintain a world-class workforce. 
 Read more >>



Mission Support
Raytheon is a world leader in mission support and maintenance, integration and modernization, design, fabrication and contract manufacturing. 
 Read more >>



Innovations
Manipulating atoms to build better satellites. Coding computer data onto particles of light. Finding ways to conserve and protect the world's power supply.
 Read more >>




